
= CAPABILITY (OPERATIONAL AND SYSTEM) =

=== DEFINITION ===

A Capability is the ability of the System to provide a service that supports the achievement of high-level operational goals.


A Capability is described by scenarios and functional chains, all illustrating possible use cases. Capabilities can be used to structure the Functional Analysis.


In Logical and Physical Architectures, Capabilities are called &quot;Capability Realizations&quot;.


